title.narrative: Increased usefulness of the budget as a strategic policy instrument, as a result of improvements in its formulation process, content and presentation.

baseline.value: Budget poorly presented. Allocations managed on a monthly basis according to cash availability.

target.value: Transparent budget prepared on basis of medium term framework. Revisions to budget take place through due process and not on basisof cash available to Treasury

comment.narrative: The budget is made available to the general public via web and budget execution reports are also posted on the web. MTBFinformation is only recently included as supplementary information to the annual budget and linkage between the MTBF and the annualbudget is extremely weak.

actual.value: Transparent budget prepared on basis of medium term framework. Revisions to budget take place through due process and not on basisof cash available to Treasury

comment.narrative: The budget is made available to the general public via web and budget execution reports are also posted on the web. MTBFinformation is only recently included as supplementary information to the annual budget and linkage between the MTBF and the annualbudget is extremely weak.

title.narrative: Improved access, reliability and timeliness of information about budget execution, to public officials and civil society.

baseline.value: Budget reports fragmented and not widely available.

target.value: Comprehensive summary budget reports made publicly available within 6 months of budget. execution.

actual.value: Budget execution reports: monthly, quarterly and annual are published on the Central Treasury website. The last available reportwas for October 2011

title.narrative: Independent Civil Service Agency established and operational.

target.value: Agency fully operational and managing recruitment, promotion and training of Civil Servants.
